nds during their crucial first years of resettlement in the United States and Canada and asylum in Germany. All three countries offer a legal solution to displacement, while simultaneously minoritizing newcomers through policies that fail to recognize their histories, aspirations, and personhood. The United States stands out for its emphasis on “self-sufficiency” that integrates refugees into American poverty, which, by design, is populated by people of color and marked by stagnation. Gowayed argues that refugee human capital is less an attribute of newcomers than a product of the same racist welfare systems that have long shaped the contours of national belonging.Centering the human experience of displacement, Refuge shines needed light on how countries structure the potential of people, new arrivals or otherwise, within their borders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRefugeeszCanadaxSocial conditions. 0aRefugeeszGermanyxSocial conditions. 0aRefugeeszSyriaxSocial conditions. 0aRefugeeszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 70(DE-588)4003338-70(DE-627)1063898900(DE-576)208851194aAsylrecht2gnd 70(DE-588)4017604-60(DE-627)1063291030(DE-576)208920668aFlüchtling2gnd 70(DE-588)4106468-90(DE-627)1045846100(DE-576)209414839aSyrer2gnd 70(DE-588)4123761-40(DE-627)1042126590(DE-576)209562455aMigrationspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4127746-60(DE-627)1041517060(DE-576)209596201aAsylbewerber2gnd 70(DE-588)4140484-10(DE-627)10562750X0(DE-576)209703180aDisplaced Person2gnd 70(DE-588)4162051-30(DE-627)1048191540(DE-576)209870583aInternationale Migration2gnd 70(DE-588)4199676-80(DE-627)1051794850(DE-576)210130229aAsylpolitik2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aAdult.  aArabic pop music.  aAtheism.  aAvailability.  aBashar al-Assad.  aBasic income.  aBill 